   "source": [
    "# Phase II: Data Collection and Exploratory Data Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3175b0d0-c16e-4f2e-b4f1-b5ab277e8cbc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Research Question(s):**\n",
    "- Main question: How does distance, passenger volume, and carrier type affect average airfare prices in U.S. nonstop flight markets?\n",
    "- Secondary questions:\n",
    "   - How does airfare change as flight distance increases? Are shorter flights more expensive per mile than longer ones?\n",
    "   - Is there a relationship between passenger count and average fare (for example, do more popular routes tend to have lower fares due to competition)?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "951a1bb4-70f8-4ae3-b86a-8586722d029a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Data Source\n",
    "- US Airline Flight Routes and Fares 1993–2024, provided by the Bureau of Transportation Statistics (BTS).  \n",
    "- Available on Kaggle: [US Airline Flight Routes and Fares Dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/bhavikjikadara/us-airline-flight-routes-and-fares-1993-2024)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why this dataset?**\n",
    "- It provides detailed fare and passenger data for thousands of U.S. flight routes over time, allowing us to explore how distance, competition, and market structure influence airfare pricing."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "4af33791-82a1-4c2e-b55e-95c6f57d9657",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\n",
    "import duckdb\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n"
   ]
  },
