   "source": [
    "distance_trends = flight_df[[\"fare\", \"nsmiles\"]].dropna()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Drop invalid rows\n",
    "distance_trends = distance_trends[(distance_trends[\"fare\"] > 0) & (distance_trends[\"nsmiles\"] > 0)]\n",
    "\n",
    "distance_trends.head()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9111faa2-d5a5-4d33-b901-cb87e9ca89e2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Fitting a trend line to this data**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 41,
   "id": "ff130269-d615-4d9f-83ef-bf0c9c782e5e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Intercept: 149.23\n",
      "Coefficient: 0.0586\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "X = distance_trends[[\"nsmiles\"]]\n",
    "y = distance_trends[\"fare\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "dist_model = LinearRegression()\n",
    "dist_model.fit(X, y)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Predictions and metrics\n",
    "print(f\"Intercept: {np.round(dist_model.intercept_, 2)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Coefficient: {np.round(dist_model.coef_[0], 4)}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "47cbdaf3-b280-4f7d-ab17-37851298bc30",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Lets further analyze this trend**\\\n",
    "To do so we will calculate the correlation between the flight distance and the fare value. Then since we have performed a linear fit of the data we wil see how well this represents the data by determining the R^2 value"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 47,
   "id": "126caa91-e9d6-4c37-9b2e-4e80de965bee",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Fare correlation to distance: 0.5004065012945059\n",
      "R-squared: 0.2504\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dist_corr = distance_trends[\"fare\"].corr(distance_trends[\"nsmiles\"])\n",
    "print(f\"Fare correlation to distance: {dist_corr}\")\n",
    "r2 = np.round(dist_model.score(X, y), 4)\n",
    "print(f\"R-squared: {r2}\")\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "793061a8-b4be-4890-938d-2c4b3affe82f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Explanation of correlation and R-squared**\\\n",
    "Here the correlation is roughly 0.5. This tells us that there is a moderately positive relationship between flight distance and fare, meaning as distance increases there is also a general increase in fare.\n",
    "\n",
    "Our R-squared value is 0.25. This tells us that flight distance is responsible for around 25% of the variance in the fares.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6d819f70-25c6-4d0d-ae5b-5491e306ab75",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cleaning *cpi_per_year_df*\n",
    "Our objective is to only have the cpi_per_year_df contain the years from 1993 to 2024 for the United States only. \\ We will be doing this by elimnating all other country rows, besdies the United States, and ensuring there are no NaN values per year. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a5065a33-048e-4156-a905-38cb67cfaa4c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**graphing fare vs quarter**\\\n",
    "With this data set we want to look at how certain quarters with many holidays (such as quarter one and four) have differing airline fare prices when compared to those without many holidays. We grouped by quarters in order to allow us to access the average fare per quarter for every year and average them. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "5650bbda-8c2e-4152-a42a-e3222d5422d2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fare_quarter_df = duckdb.sql(\"\"\"SELECT AVG(fare) AS average_fare, quarter FROM flight_df GROUP BY quarter\"\"\").df()\n",
    "sns.barplot(data = fare_quarter_df, x = \"quarter\", y = \"average_fare\")\n",
    "plt.ylim(213, 225)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.title(\"Average Fare by Quarter\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Quarter\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Average Fare\", rotation = 0,labelpad = 10);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a0a1659a-8452-45a9-95ad-6c35e41e4961",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Findings**\\\n",
    "This graph demonstrates that airlines increase the prices for flights during the start of the year (the first and second quarters). This is vastly different than what we expected since we predicted that the fourth quarter would have the highest fares. This is very unexpected for us since we figured holidays like christmas, thanksgiving and new years would increase travel rates and fares. The data clearly does not support this claim since the first half of the year has the most costly airline tickets. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "23447217-e21b-4269-8beb-752f27785691",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Time series (Fare over time) 1993 - 2024\n",
    "*Formula to account for inflation: Adjusted Value = (Nominal Value * CPI\\_BaseYear) / CPI\\_Current*\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "9cba82d5-ee5d-41b7-85a3-e3c2f0ce3060",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "   Year        fare fare_with_inflation\n",
      "0  1993  214.472632          214.317734\n",
      "1  1994  217.611944          246.161569\n",
      "2  1996  204.900283          206.180978\n",
      "3  1997  208.105858          262.572663\n",
      "4  1998  210.451983          399.885194\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "present_cpi = flights_and_inflation_df.loc[flights_and_inflation_df['Year'] == 2024, 'CPI_per_year'].iloc[0]\n",
    "flights_and_inflation_df['fare_with_inflation'] = (flights_and_inflation_df['fare'] * present_cpi) / flights_and_inflation_df['CPI_per_year']\n",
    "\n",
    "avg_fare_by_year_inflation = flights_and_inflation_df.groupby('Year')[['fare', 'fare_with_inflation']].mean().reset_index()\n",
    "print(avg_fare_by_year_inflation.head())\n"
   ]
  },
